- Not tonight.

16:32.825 --> 16:36.158
I've got to get home early,
make some comfort food, get some sleep,

16:36.228 --> 16:38.093
get better for tomorrow.

16:38.163 --> 16:39.357
I got cleared for tonight,

16:39.431 --> 16:41.365
now I've got to check with Karen
about tomorrow?

16:41.433 --> 16:45.028
- Spoken like a true married man.
- Hey, it could happen to you, too.

16:45.104 --> 16:48.733
Didn't Emory make the
"Top 20 Hottest Women in New York" list?

16:48.807 --> 16:50.069
We're just having fun, pal, okay?

16:50.142 --> 16:52.406
Don't drag me
into your own little personal hell.

16:52.478 --> 16:54.639
The guys that say
they don't want to get married,

16:54.713 --> 16:57.011
they're the ones who surprise you.

16:57.082 --> 16:59.573
So, since you've been
on the wedding bandwagon since day one,

16:59.651 --> 17:01.744
you must secretly dread the actual event.

17:01.854 --> 17:05.756
- You know, there's still time to back out.
- I'm not you.

17:05.824 --> 17:08.884
What the hell are you drinking?
It smells like an Indian restaurant.

17:08.961 --> 17:11.691
Cold remedy.
Credit-card girl told me about it.

17:12.964 --> 17:15.525
Still can't believe
someone stole your identity.

17:15.601 --> 17:18.092
I mean, of all the identities out there
to steal, who'd want to steal yours?

17:19.338 --> 17:24.366
- Hope they're living large on your dime.
- Nice. Good friend.

17:43.162 --> 17:47.531
There was an attempt to use your card
for $700 at the Mystery Box.

17:47.599 --> 17:49.362
Seriously?

17:49.435 --> 17:51.801
Unless you throw in a night
with the cashier and some dolls,

17:51.870 --> 17:53.303
how do you spend that much
at a store like that?

17:53.372 --> 17:55.704
I don't know what kind
of store it is, sir.

17:55.774 --> 17:58.402
Oh, come on.
They don't have them in San Francisco?

18:02.347 --> 18:05.316
Yeah. Sure.

18:06.285 --> 18:09.584
Which is why I was certain
this wasn't your charge.

18:10.422 --> 18:12.788
Because I don't give off
a sexually adventurous vibe?

18:14.560 --> 18:15.720
No.

18:16.161 --> 18:18.561
Because you were sneezing profusely
into my eardrums

18:18.630 --> 18:21.463
about the time the charge was made.

18:21.533 --> 18:23.501
Nice work, Detective David.

18:24.002 --> 18:27.199
Okay, the big plasma TV charge,
that's mine.

18:27.272 --> 18:29.240
You know, sometimes
you just have to splurge

18:29.308 --> 18:31.776
and get yourself something
that you enjoy, live a little.

18:31.844 --> 18:34.438
Especially after a
long day at the office.

18:34.513 --> 18:37.744
I just have a cup of <i>chai.</i>
I mean, coffee.

18:39.885 --> 18:42.285
You're not fooling anyone.

18:42.354 --> 18:47.587
You Californians are all into your tofu
and your sandals.

18:47.659 --> 18:49.320
You're probably a Dead Head.

18:50.896 --> 18:52.625
Am I right, dude?

18:52.931 --> 18:55.161
Actually, I just prefer jazz.

18:56.935 --> 18:59.733
All right, here's the question.

18:59.805 --> 19:04.504
JalapeÃ±os in your grilled cheese,
kicker or overkill?

19:08.013 --> 19:10.504
- Kicker?
- Absolutely.

19:22.161 --> 19:25.324
<i>Hello? You still there?</i>

19:28.033 --> 19:30.160
And the charge to Delicious Delights?

19:30.235 --> 19:32.465
Biggest amaretto cake known to man.

19:32.538 --> 19:34.665
My mother was having a lousy week.

19:34.740 --> 19:38.972
Sometimes you just want
to show someone you care. Right?

19:39.044 --> 19:40.602
Right.

19:40.679 --> 19:45.082
Okay, the last one. Um...
The charges from New World Video.

19:46.952 --> 19:51.013
Those were late fees.
I rented <i>The Notebook.</i> Don't laugh.

19:51.990 --> 19:55.084
Why would I laugh? I love that movie.

19:55.160 --> 19:56.593
<i>I don't normally watch chick flicks,</i>

19:56.662 --> 19:58.892
and I don't even know
if that classifies as one,

19:58.964 --> 20:02.798
but you ever watch a movie and just think
that's the way things should be?

20:03.702 --> 20:07.934
Like, someone puts themselves out there
for someone or something,

20:08.006 --> 20:11.237
and either they get it or they don't.

20:11.310 --> 20:12.572
But love's worth it.

20:13.879 --> 20:16.370
Hi, this is Courtney Reese from CITYone.
May I help you?

20:16.448 --> 20:19.042
I think that will
take care of it for now.

20:19.117 --> 20:22.575
<i>If any more charges come in,</i>
<i>I'll be in touch with you.</i>

20:22.654 --> 20:23.951
Great.

20:24.022 --> 20:27.651
I failed to mention that you qualify
for our platinum card.

20:27.726 --> 20:29.694
If you agree to a four-year term,

20:29.761 --> 20:33.094
I can get you
a very attractive interest rate.

20:33.165 --> 20:35.565
Four years? That's quite a commitment.

20:35.834 --> 20:37.529
Just think of all the
ribs you could eat, sir.

20:37.603 --> 20:38.661
You don't need to call me "sir."

20:38.737 --> 20:40.864
I mean, hell, you know more about me
than my own mother.

20:41.106 --> 20:43.006
- Granger's fine.
<i>- All right.</i>

20:43.775 --> 20:48.269
Granger, be sure to contact us
if you want an upgrade,

20:48.347 --> 20:51.839
and you should be expecting
a new card soon. Thank you.

20:55.354 --> 20:56.582
Granger?

21:01.827 --> 21:03.124
<i>Jennifer David. May I help you?</i>

21:03.195 --> 21:05.163
I just wanted to thank you
for the cold remedy.

21:05.230 --> 21:09.360
<i>It really did the trick.</i>
<i>It's me, Granger, by the way.</i>

21:09.434 --> 21:13.962
I'm so glad. I was actually going to ask
how you were feeling.

21:14.039 --> 21:16.769
Well, we do what we can do to help, sir.

21:20.612 --> 21:22.375
<i>Granger, good night.</i>

21:25.083 --> 21:26.778
Be careful, Priya.

21:38.797 --> 21:41.357
- No, Papa.
- I'm sorry. Sorry, sorry.

21:51.443 --> 21:54.844
Eh? This is the bathroom.

21:54.913 --> 21:56.278
Do you need to use it?

21:56.348 --> 21:57.940
- Have a look.
- No.

21:59.685 --> 22:03.485
This is my bedroom. Our bedroom.

22:04.556 --> 22:08.219
We're buying a brand-new double bed
with a brass headboard.

22:08.293 --> 22:11.751
- Mother has already picked it out.
- Yes.

22:12.931 --> 22:14.626
Oh! Uh...

22:15.734 --> 22:19.966
Perhaps one day we'll have our own house
if we both work hard enough.

22:22.274 --> 22:24.469
But we wouldn't have
my mother's fine cooking every day.

22:25.677 --> 22:28.737
- She has many things to teach you.
- Yes.

22:35.087 --> 22:38.488
So what sort of things do you like to do?

22:38.557 --> 22:41.424
You know,
if you could live your life any way,

22:41.493 --> 22:43.484
what would you want?

22:43.562 --> 22:47.692
I'm pretty content
with things as they are.

22:47.766 --> 22:49.529
Once I'm married...

22:50.936 --> 22:54.303
We're married, I'll have everything.

22:55.240 --> 22:58.732
A wife at home,
a beautifully tended garden,

22:59.978 --> 23:03.175
when you're not busy
with our children, of course.

23:04.750 --> 23:09.312
I love my job.
And as for children, I'm only 22.

23:10.555 --> 23:14.992
There is time for us to live a little,
don't you think so?

23:16.194 --> 23:18.856
But we will live a lot right here.

23:32.978 --> 23:38.473
Look at that. That's not sexy?
That's what spots are these days, sex.

23:39.851 --> 23:43.878
I have some vacation time,
so I was thinking.

23:43.955 --> 23:45.286
I'm gonna go with you on your trip.

23:45.357 --> 23:49.521
Oh, and I thought that I...
Well, I thought that I could wear these.

23:53.298 --> 23:54.629
You don't want to go.

23:54.699 --> 23:59.500
You know, it's gonna be cold, foggy.
I'll be in a hotel room all day.

23:59.604 --> 24:02.630
You're gonna need
some in-room entertainment.

24:02.707 --> 24:04.607
I'm on business, Emory.

24:05.610 --> 24:08.636
This account is important to us.
I can't be...

24:11.183 --> 24:12.275
Fine.

24:14.419 --> 24:16.910
- Fine.
- Em, I'm sorry.

24:16.988 --> 24:21.823
No, you know what? Actually, I think
I'll take Mark Bailey up on his lunch.

24:23.195 --> 24:26.528
I think he has a jet that he takes
to his oceanfront in Bermuda.

24:26.598 --> 24:29.795
- You're trying to tell me something here?
- Yeah.

24:29.868 --> 24:32.098
Nobody says no to Emory Banks.

24:38.076 --> 24:39.634
<i>He has an amazing voice,</i>

24:39.711 --> 24:44.080
<i>he says the most interesting things,</i>
<i>he's funny,</i>

24:44.149 --> 24:45.707
<i>and he has such kind eyes.</i>

24:45.784 --> 24:49.083
You looked up his picture?
- What if we were really soul mates?

24:49.154 --> 24:51.952
Listen, you're just anxious about Vikram.

24:52.090 --> 24:55.457
Trust me. When I was marrying Babu,
I thought my life was gonna end.

24:55.560 --> 24:59.223
I mean, how can two people who
don't even know each other get married?

24:59.297 --> 25:01.663
But then, a few months later,
we were laughing

25:01.733 --> 25:07.603
at something really silly I'd done,
and I realized I'd fallen in love with him.

25:07.672 --> 25:09.867
How sweet.

25:09.941 --> 25:14.605
And it's easier than falling in love
with some random voice on the phone.

25:14.679 --> 25:18.274
And seriously, this guy lives in America.

25:18.350 --> 25:21.012
- There's no point.
- I know.

25:28.493 --> 25:29.551
I've got to meet Karen.

25:29.628 --> 25:32.688
Oh, and she made me swear
there'd be no strippers

25:32.764 --> 25:34.527
at the bachelor party.

25:34.599 --> 25:39.298
Well, if Karen said no strippers,
that means no strippers.

25:39.371 --> 25:41.566
Only, I really want strippers.

25:44.843 --> 25:48.210
She didn't say anything
about exotic dancers, did she?

25:48.280 --> 25:49.542
No, she did not.

25:55.253 --> 25:57.687
Mr. Granger, what can I do for you?

25:57.756 --> 26:01.192
Hey, I just wanted to alert you
a future charge.

26:01.259 --> 26:04.626
When Exotic Minx shows up, that's mine.

26:05.163 --> 26:06.528
I think a pet should make you happy.

26:07.699 --> 26:08.757
Do I seem sad?

26:09.134 --> 26:12.626
Not always, but, you know,
you buy a lot of things,

26:12.704 --> 26:15.605
and people do that
to make themselves happy.

26:16.641 --> 26:18.734
<i>- I eat chocolate.</i>
- Thanks, Doc.

26:19.177 --> 26:21.145
I'm actually hiring dancers
for a bachelor party.

26:21.212 --> 26:22.509
You know, before the big wedding.

26:24.015 --> 26:25.175
Are you getting married?

26:25.450 --> 26:27.611
Me? No, no, no, no.
It's for my buddy, Charlie.

26:28.787 --> 26:30.721
Party's probably gonna cost
a couple grand.

26:30.789 --> 26:34.987
Wow! So what happens
at these bachelor parties?

26:35.594 --> 26:37.687
The usual things you hear about.

26:37.829 --> 26:41.356
But, really, it's just a symbolic,
platonic representation

26:41.433 --> 26:44.163
<i>of the last adventure</i>
<i>before one commits to marriage.</i>

26:44.903 --> 26:48.202
I think it's actually a necessary journey,
a rite of passage, if you will.

26:48.473 --> 26:51.306
- I think everyone should have one.
<i>- Me, too.</i>

26:53.211 --> 26:56.703
Hey, listen, I'm going
to San Francisco next week for work,

26:56.781 --> 27:00.376
and, you know, I thought maybe we could
get together and discuss my options.

27:02.721 --> 27:04.916
Financial things can get so complicated
over the phone.

27:05.023 --> 27:07.856
It's not really company policy
to do these things in person.

27:07.926 --> 27:11.293
<i>Aren't you supposed to keep</i>
<i>the customer satisfied?</i>

27:12.831 --> 27:15.356
Yeah, we love to satisfy,

27:15.433 --> 27:19.096
but I may not be
in San Francisco next week.

27:19.571 --> 27:21.436
I may be in...

27:23.608 --> 27:26.475
I may be out of town
for a relative's birthday.

27:28.947 --> 27:31.415
I have to go back to work now.

27:32.050 --> 27:35.850
Okay. Well, you know,
you have my number if you stay in town.

27:37.188 --> 27:40.089
Wow!
You can really see David Bowie tonight.

27:40.759 --> 27:42.989
- Sorry?
<i>- In the moon. You've never heard that?</i>

27:43.328 --> 27:45.728
You know, when there's a full moon,
you can see David Bowie's face.

27:47.432 --> 27:49.764
Always...
Well, I thought it was Mick Jagger.

27:50.135 --> 27:53.696
No, no, no. It's clearly Bowie.
You know, the cheekbones, the chin.

27:53.772 --> 27:56.536
Well, thank you for using CITYone Bank.

27:58.276 --> 27:59.766
Have a nice day.

28:01.079 --> 28:02.410
Good night.

28:15.894 --> 28:17.555
To the guy who said
he's never been anywhere,

28:17.629 --> 28:20.792
I give you, Charlie Hendricks, the world.

28:20.865 --> 28:22.662
Miss Russia.

28:22.734 --> 28:25.601
- I'm from Ukraine.
- She's from Ukraine.

28:27.205 --> 28:28.263
Miss Japan.

28:34.145 --> 28:37.444
Miss...
From somewhere where they wear clogs.

28:38.083 --> 28:40.210
No, no, no, no. This guy.

28:43.755 --> 28:46.588
You deserve it, buddy.
You deserve the world.

28:46.658 --> 28:47.989
Charlie!

28:48.059 --> 28:49.788
Ladies, come on in.

29:00.271 --> 29:01.602
Thank you.

29:07.445 --> 29:11.711
- Oh. That's too much.
- I'll pay, <i>Baba.</i>

29:13.118 --> 29:14.312
Don't be ridiculous.

29:14.385 --> 29:17.115
Why not let her?
She makes more than you.

29:27.398 --> 29:28.558
Aha!

29:28.633 --> 29:30.999
You will make a beautiful bride.

29:33.238 --> 29:34.865
Thank you, <i>Baba.</i>

29:36.407 --> 29:40.935
We'll take it. Oh, my <i>beta.</i>

29:45.650 --> 29:47.140
- Hello?
- Granger?

29:48.219 --> 29:51.052
- Jennifer!
- Sounds like you're having fun.

29:51.122 --> 29:52.487
Oh, it's a full-on rager.

29:53.825 --> 29:55.725
<i>It's Charlie's big night,</i>

29:55.794 --> 29:57.284
and the natives are a bit restless.

29:57.362 --> 30:01.196
Next week, it turns out that I will
be able to meet you before the party,

30:01.266 --> 30:05.293
so we can discuss the upgrade
we were talking about

30:06.137 --> 30:08.765
when we were talking, before.

30:08.940 --> 30:10.305
<i>That sounds great.</i>

30:10.809 --> 30:12.299
I'd like that.

30:13.011 --> 30:15.445
- It's the credit-card girl.
- Nice.

30:16.147 --> 30:17.876
I'll be in San Francisco on Thursday,

30:17.949 --> 30:21.316
so maybe we can meet
at the Hawksin Grand Hotel?

30:22.120 --> 30:23.280
<i>- You know where that is?</i>
- Word.

30:23.354 --> 30:25.219
Okay, let's say 6:00.

30:25.290 --> 30:28.020
I'll be the dashing New Yorker
with unlimited credit.

30:28.092 --> 30:30.026
It's a date.

30:30.094 --> 30:35.293
I mean, Thursday is the date of the day
when we'll meet.

30:35.366 --> 30:36.697
<i>I'll see you then.</i>

30:46.611 --> 30:48.806
You know you're crazy, right?

30:49.013 --> 30:50.275
Hmm.

30:50.348 --> 30:53.613
What if this guy turns out to be
from a bad family and kidnaps you

30:53.685 --> 30:57.781
and makes you clean their toilets and,
like, clean their dirty cats and all?

30:57.856 --> 31:01.121
Then he's in real trouble.
I'm not a good cleaner.

31:01.192 --> 31:03.524
<i>Bhaiya,</i> Mumbai Airport.
Thank you, <i>bhaiya.</i>

31:21.913 --> 31:23.437
Thanks, <i>bhaiya.</i>

31:30.255 --> 31:31.950
You know you're playing with matches.

31:32.023 --> 31:34.514
Fire? Why can't I have a little of that?

31:34.592 --> 31:38.255
Why can't I have
just one amazing last adventure

31:38.329 --> 31:40.797
before I come back to Vikram?
This is my bachelor party.

31:40.865 --> 31:42.628
I can't believe you're going all this way

31:42.700 --> 31:46.761
to see if this deranged guy is your Tom,
Richard, Harry, Hank soul mate guy.

31:46.838 --> 31:49.739
- I don't know.
- I promise you, I'll be back in two pieces.

31:49.807 --> 31:52.901
- You better.
- Wish the stars to shine bright on me.

31:57.181 --> 32:00.480
<i>Mummy, Papa, please don't faint,</i>

32:00.551 --> 32:04.647
<i>but by the time you hear this,</i>
<i>I'll be on my way to America.</i>

32:04.722 --> 32:08.385
<i>I know I should have told you,</i>
<i>but it was a last-minute decision.</i>

32:08.526 --> 32:13.828
<i>I left my heart</i>

32:17.001 --> 32:19.868
<i>In San Francisco</i>

32:26.210 --> 32:29.873
<i>I've decided to attend</i>
<i>father's cousin sister's birthday party</i>

32:29.948 --> 32:34.510
<i>in Palo Alto.</i>
<i>It's been a long time since I've seen them.</i>

32:34.585 --> 32:39.318
<i>I'll send everyone your regards.</i>
<i>And see you in five days, maybe.</i>

32:40.325 --> 32:41.587
Ouch!

32:42.527 --> 32:45.690
<i>And please don't panic,</i>
<i>I'm using my own savings.</i>

32:46.764 --> 32:51.030
<i>Papa, remember how you always wanted
your little daughter to travel</i>

32:51.102 --> 32:54.128
<i>and learn different cultures?</i>

32:54.205 --> 32:55.638
<i>This is your gift to me.</i>

32:55.974 --> 33:00.434
<i>The morning fog</i>

33:00.511 --> 33:04.948
<i>May chill the air</i>

33:06.818 --> 33:09.309
Hello. Welcome to Hawksin Hotel.

33:09.387 --> 33:11.116
- Have you got your passport on you?
- Yeah.

33:11.189 --> 33:14.249
Great. Thank you.

33:14.325 --> 33:16.623
You're the behind-the-scenes
creative guy.

33:16.694 --> 33:20.892
Yes, yes. No, and he knows why.

33:20.965 --> 33:22.660
Mr. Hawksin.

33:22.734 --> 33:24.998
Well, well.
Look who decided to get off their butts

33:25.069 --> 33:26.229
and come fight for the job.

33:26.304 --> 33:27.635
Never turn down a second chance.

33:27.705 --> 33:30.799
The rooms are fantastic, by the way.
Thank you, sir.

33:30.875 --> 33:33.571
- May I speak, sir?
- Only to say thank you.

33:33.644 --> 33:36.112
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

33:36.180 --> 33:39.206
- We're gonna knock your socks off.
- And then he ruins it by speaking again.

33:39.283 --> 33:41.979
Didn't we talk about that?
Didn't I ask you not to speak so much?

33:42.053 --> 33:44.613
Didn't I tell you to learn to listen?
Don't you want to be a nice boy?

33:44.689 --> 33:49.422
Didn't I tell you to be more like him?
Here, watch this. Your hair is on fire.

33:52.096 --> 33:55.156
But I don't want a Honda.
Learn from this.

33:59.437 --> 34:01.632
Could you shut up? He doesn't like you.

34:02.807 --> 34:04.172
He likes me.

34:11.215 --> 34:14.775
I can't believe you're hooking up
with the credit-card girl.

34:15.820 --> 34:20.052
No, wait, I believe it.
You're gutsy, pal.

34:20.391 --> 34:25.293
I mean, what if she turns out
to be this lonely housewife

34:25.797 --> 34:29.494
with four kids and bad teeth and gout?

34:29.567 --> 34:30.931
It's just drinks.

34:47.051 --> 34:48.518
Vibe?
- I got a good vibe.

34:48.585 --> 34:49.678
Oh!

34:50.521 --> 34:52.580
Just your type, 1 o'clock behind you.

34:52.657 --> 34:54.318
- This one?
- Yeah.

34:56.828 --> 34:58.193
Seriously.

35:01.532 --> 35:02.794
That's her.

35:04.335 --> 35:07.031
- I'm going in.
- Good luck.

35:20.918 --> 35:23.580
- Excuse me, Granger Woodruff.
- Hi.

35:24.489 --> 35:28.789
- You're not Jennifer David?
- No. But I wish I was.

35:30.828 --> 35:33.092
Sorry, I thought you were somebody else.

35:37.935 --> 35:41.098
Excuse me, ladies...

35:42.773 --> 35:45.606
You're not Jennifer David?

35:45.676 --> 35:48.372
- You didn't even talk to him?
<i>- I couldn't, Zia.</i>

35:48.613 --> 35:52.105
I was frozen, stuck, like gum.

35:52.216 --> 35:53.774
Okay, so your crazy crush is over.

35:53.851 --> 35:56.843
Just come home, we'll watch
<i>Fatal Attraction</i> and you'll be fine.

35:56.921 --> 35:58.081
Listen, this guy was no good.

35:58.156 --> 36:00.989
I'm sure he lied about those charges
and he spends money like a maniac.

36:01.058 --> 36:02.320
He's not a liar.

36:02.393 --> 36:05.590
And then he just, like, covers it all up.
It's just much better that you run now

36:05.663 --> 36:07.654
than be hot-glued to the floor later.

36:07.732 --> 36:09.393
Maybe I expected too much.

36:09.467 --> 36:11.992
<i>Besides, he didn't even</i>
<i>get a chance to meet me.</i>

36:12.069 --> 36:14.333
<i>If he did...</i>

36:14.405 --> 36:17.203
You know, there was something
magical in our talk, Zia.

36:17.275 --> 36:19.266
- I promise you.
<i>- Yes.</i>

36:19.343 --> 36:23.211
I do think that the American slang
for that is "bullshit."

36:23.814 --> 36:25.941
<i>- Just come home, okay?</i>
- Bye.

36:32.557 --> 36:34.684
So, your girl stood you up.

36:34.926 --> 36:37.656
Come out to dinner with me and Karen's
best friend, it'll be good for a laugh.

36:37.728 --> 36:40.288
Discussing the intimate details
of bridesmaids' dresses

36:40.364 --> 36:41.922
isn't my idea of a good time.

36:41.999 --> 36:46.299
But you, my friend, you've got to take
this stuff seriously. It's your wedding.

36:48.005 --> 36:50.405
Let me know how the bouquets work out.

36:53.911 --> 36:56.880
Sorry. You okay?

36:59.083 --> 37:02.712
- Gray...
- No, no, no, no. You... Do you see color?

37:03.187 --> 37:07.920
Look, red bag. Red...

37:13.431 --> 37:17.731
Keep the legs elevated.
I think you're gonna live.

37:18.536 --> 37:20.868
- I'm all right.
- I'm really sorry.

37:21.272 --> 37:24.332
- I didn't see you.
- No, I... I wasn't looking, I was...

37:24.408 --> 37:27.673
No, no, no. It's my fault. I feel awful.

37:29.280 --> 37:31.180
I wish you wouldn't...

37:32.416 --> 37:36.079
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- No, I mean...

37:36.787 --> 37:39.119
I wish you wouldn't feel awful.

37:42.426 --> 37:45.953
So, are you here on vacation?

37:47.632 --> 37:54.470
Yeah, from India. I'm visiting a relative
at Palo Alto, just for a party.

37:55.873 --> 37:58.239
Hey, I know this might sound odd,

37:58.309 --> 38:01.244
and considering the dangers
of being with me and all,

38:01.312 --> 38:03.473
but you hungry?

38:04.181 --> 38:08.242
I was gonna go out to dinner,
and I thought you might want to come.

38:09.620 --> 38:10.951
Oh! Um...

38:14.492 --> 38:19.828
That'll be nice, but only if it's ribs.

38:20.231 --> 38:24.998
I read about this place in my guidebook.
You do like meat, don't you?

38:27.305 --> 38:28.294
Yeah.

38:30.207 --> 38:31.606
Mmm.

38:31.942 --> 38:35.002
They're delicious, thank you.

38:35.513 --> 38:38.311
Granger Woodruff, by the way.

38:39.750 --> 38:41.877
Hello, Granger, I'm Priya Sethi.

38:42.753 --> 38:45.483
Okay, Priya. You've got to just dig in.

38:45.890 --> 38:47.824
Okay? Don't...
Don't worry about getting messy.

38:47.892 --> 38:50.326
Just get it all over you.

38:50.394 --> 38:51.622
Okay.

38:53.397 --> 38:55.729
So, what do you do in Mumbai?

38:58.269 --> 39:00.965
- I'm a nurse. Yeah.
- Nurse.

39:01.372 --> 39:03.135
It's quite nice.

39:04.809 --> 39:06.504
- Good food.
- So...

39:07.311 --> 39:10.007
- Is this your first trip to America?
- Yeah.

39:10.081 --> 39:14.381
I always wanted to come,
and it's much more than I've expected.

39:15.653 --> 39:18.281
- You're on vacation?
- I wish.

39:19.323 --> 39:23.692
I'm actually here for a business campaign.
I have this huge presentation next week.

39:23.861 --> 39:27.957
Hey, maybe you can help me.
I mean, you're international clientele.

39:28.866 --> 39:31.266
What attracted you to the Hawksin Hotel?

39:34.004 --> 39:37.667
- A friend told me about it.
- So you go on personal recommendations?

39:37.875 --> 39:40.935
I mean, do you ever just
want to take a chance?

39:41.445 --> 39:45.347
You know, like... Like the feeling
of trying something different?

39:45.416 --> 39:49.716
I take chances, but usually
I can never afford them.

39:49.787 --> 39:53.655
Charge it, you know, charge everything.
Just pay for it later.

39:54.625 --> 39:57.253
Just don't let it get stolen.

39:58.028 --> 40:00.019
Did someone steal your card?

40:00.131 --> 40:03.032
I have my ace credit-card girl
working on it.

40:03.100 --> 40:07.059
She was actually supposed to meet me,
but she blew me off.

40:07.438 --> 40:11.272
Yeah. When someone opts out
of a prearranged appointment.

40:13.844 --> 40:17.041
- For what purpose were you to meet her?
- Just casual.

40:17.148 --> 40:18.979
She sounded nice.

40:19.517 --> 40:22.645
But her friends probably warned her
about meeting a complete stranger,

40:22.720 --> 40:24.881
and she probably thought I was psychotic,

40:24.955 --> 40:27.981
or maybe she just took
one look at me and ran.

40:30.861 --> 40:33.728
Excuse me, I...
I need to go to the restroom.

40:36.066 --> 40:40.526
Zia, it's me. Could you please connect me
to Granger? It's 4593330555.

40:40.604 --> 40:43.835
Why do you want to talk to him?
I thought you blew him out.

40:43.908 --> 40:48.777
I don't want him to think I was rude, and
actually, we're having dinner right now.

40:49.346 --> 40:53.373
- What? You told him you're Jennifer?
<i>- No. It... It doesn't matter.</i>

40:53.551 --> 40:55.815
<i>We're meeting as our real selves,</i>
<i>and it's better this way.</i>

40:55.886 --> 40:58.252
<i>So, could you please</i>
<i>connect me to Granger?</i>

40:58.322 --> 41:00.051
Priya, this can lead to no good.

41:00.124 --> 41:05.061
Or it could lead to the perfect romantic
moment under the Golden Gate Bridge.

41:05.629 --> 41:08.154
Listen, honestly, you've lost your head.

41:11.268 --> 41:12.428
Hello?

41:12.503 --> 41:14.596
Hello, Granger. It's Jennifer David.

41:14.672 --> 41:17.402
Hey! Is everything okay?

41:18.075 --> 41:20.908
I'm afraid when you didn't show up,
I signed up with the Visa girl.

41:20.978 --> 41:22.707
<i>She threw in a hat.</i>

41:23.447 --> 41:26.416
I wanted to apologize
about not making our appointment.

41:26.484 --> 41:29.419
It turns out I'm out of town, after all.

41:29.487 --> 41:32.149
That's cool. Maybe next time, then.

41:32.623 --> 41:36.150
Very good. It...
It sounds like you're at a restaurant.

41:36.227 --> 41:40.664
<i>- Teddy's Barbecue. You been?</i>
- Yeah. I was there recently.

41:40.731 --> 41:44.997
Excellent ribs.
It's very romantic, isn't it?

41:47.071 --> 41:52.566
Yeah. You know, since you stood me up,
I'm actually here with a nice girl.

41:53.210 --> 41:55.269
Of course, I did smack her in the head,

41:55.346 --> 41:57.644
which I wouldn't have done
if you did show up.

41:57.715 --> 42:01.151
Well, have fun with your friend.
I'm sure she's quite lovely.

42:01.785 --> 42:07.951
Inside and out. Not to be conceited for her.
Enjoy your evening.

42:08.359 --> 42:11.419
- Good night.
- Good night.

42:26.744 --> 42:29.235
Oh, wow, she's so good.

42:32.416 --> 42:37.046
- Hello?
- Hello, sister. How're things there?

42:37.821 --> 42:39.914
<i>- Ji,</i> ask.
- Okay.

42:40.491 --> 42:41.753
What I wanted to know, sister...

42:41.825 --> 42:43.816
Anji, just switch it off,
I can't hear a word.

42:45.095 --> 42:47.393
Has finally Priya arrived there?

42:48.065 --> 42:50.966
Priya? No. Priya isn't here.

42:51.235 --> 42:52.429
Priya is not there?

42:53.737 --> 42:57.264
One minute. One minute. Supposing...
Supposing she wants to give a surprise?

42:57.341 --> 42:59.901
- Hang up. Hang up.
- Wait a minute, sister. What?

42:59.977 --> 43:01.911
- Hang up the phone.
- She might want to give a surprise.

43:01.979 --> 43:03.571
- Hang up. Hang up.
- I just can't hang up just like that.

43:03.647 --> 43:04.636
- Quiet!
- Hang up.

43:05.783 --> 43:07.148
<i>Haan,</i> sister. In case Priya...

43:08.285 --> 43:09.980
In case Priya calls up,

43:10.054 --> 43:12.249
just tell her that...
Just inform us, okay?

43:12.323 --> 43:15.918
Stop it, <i>ji,</i> stop it.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, hello, phone...

43:15.993 --> 43:18.052
He sounded very confused.

43:27.538 --> 43:30.837
- Woodruff. Well...
- Mr. Hawksin.

43:33.077 --> 43:35.307
I'd like you to meet my wife, Haejin.

43:35.613 --> 43:37.171
- Hello.
- Hi. Granger.

43:37.615 --> 43:42.575
I'd like to introduce you to a very good
friend of mine, Priya Sethi.

43:42.953 --> 43:43.977
She's from Mumbai.

43:44.054 --> 43:46.318
Mumbai.
That's the New York of India, right?

43:46.390 --> 43:48.551
I hear there's quite an explosion
of jobs there.

43:48.626 --> 43:51.925
I like to think of New York
as the Mumbai of America,

43:51.996 --> 43:53.964
both with talented human resources.

43:58.202 --> 44:01.501
- That's so sweet.
- Very impressive.

44:01.872 --> 44:04.238
Well, we opened a hotel in Mumbai in '98,

44:04.308 --> 44:06.776
the Hawksin Standard at Nariman Point.
Do you know it?

44:06.844 --> 44:10.610
It's beautiful. The use of
steel and glass is breathtaking.

44:10.714 --> 44:14.241
Thank you. We think so, too.
You're lovely. Isn't she?

44:14.618 --> 44:17.109
- She's lovely.
- Yes, she is.

44:17.421 --> 44:20.618
Has he invited you to our little shindig?

44:20.691 --> 44:23.922
- I was just about to, actually.
- Good, good. Hold on a second.

44:23.994 --> 44:26.827
Mary Pat, this young lady has come
a very long way to be with us.

44:26.897 --> 44:29.764
Would you give her our nicest room,
with fruit basket, extra chocolates,

44:29.833 --> 44:31.357
flowers every day? On my account.

44:31.435 --> 44:33.960
Very good, Mr. Hawksin.
- That's very generous, sir.

44:34.038 --> 44:35.437
Don't be silly.

44:35.606 --> 44:40.407
So, we'll move you to 1740. It's a nicer
floor with its own concierge service,

44:40.477 --> 44:44.208
and I'll put you under Mr. Hawksin's name
as his guest.

44:44.281 --> 44:46.340
Thank you. That's very kind of you.

44:46.417 --> 44:49.784
Not at all. One of the pleasures
of owning places like this,

44:49.853 --> 44:52.378
doing nice things for nice people.

44:55.292 --> 44:57.317
If you'll excuse us,
we'll say our good nights.

44:57.394 --> 44:58.656
Good night.

44:58.829 --> 45:00.797
- Good night.
- Good night.

45:06.370 --> 45:08.804
Wow! I... You...

45:09.173 --> 45:12.973
You know, he really...
I've never seen him act like that before.

45:13.043 --> 45:16.012
- Yeah?
- That was amazing.

45:16.246 --> 45:17.907
No, no.
Let me just get one thing right.

45:17.981 --> 45:19.972
Aren't you supposed to be
Priya's best friend?

45:20.050 --> 45:21.312
Yes, Mr. Sethi.

45:21.385 --> 45:23.546
- Isn't she supposed to tell you everything?
- Yes.

45:23.620 --> 45:25.053
Then why aren't you telling me
where she is?

45:25.122 --> 45:26.885
Okay, maybe I should ask Miss Prasad.
Miss Prasad!

45:26.957 --> 45:28.857
No, no, no. Mr. Sethi, please.

45:29.693 --> 45:30.887
- I'll tell you.
- What?

45:30.961 --> 45:33.794
- She's gone to meet a CITYone customer.
- Okay. Where?

45:33.864 --> 45:37.231
- Mr. Granger Woodruff.
- Okay. An American?

45:38.168 --> 45:40.136
- To America? Oh, my God!
- Oh, God. No...

45:40.204 --> 45:41.899
- I should have never let her work here.
- No.

45:41.972 --> 45:45.567
No, no, no! Mr. Sethi.
I promise you, she's coming back.

45:45.642 --> 45:48.577
She had no intention to elope,
or anything of that nature.

45:48.645 --> 45:51.546
- Elope? Who is talking about elope?
- Oh, God.

45:51.615 --> 45:53.708
Oh, my God. I have to go.
I have to go and get her.

45:53.784 --> 45:56.344
- I have...
- No, no, no, Mr. Sethi! No, no!

45:56.420 --> 45:58.615
Mr. Sethi, I promise you,
she's coming back.

46:25.182 --> 46:27.412
Morning, Priya.

46:27.851 --> 46:31.480
Hey! Isn't it amazing?

46:32.990 --> 46:36.448
- I love rain.
- Yeah, yeah. It's... It's great.

46:37.461 --> 46:40.123
Hey, you're still going to meet me at
the restaurant tonight at 7:00, right?

46:40.197 --> 46:45.134
Yeah.
Hey, is this a fancy party or something?

46:45.769 --> 46:47.964
Well, you might want to wear
something nice.

46:48.038 --> 46:51.530
I mean, not nice-nice. But, you know.

46:52.075 --> 46:53.303
Yeah.

46:56.680 --> 47:01.117
Well, I have some work to do,
but I'll see you tonight.

47:01.919 --> 47:03.113
Great.

47:10.093 --> 47:12.561
<i>Welcome to San Francisco International.</i>

47:12.663 --> 47:14.221
Now, the moment we find our luggage,

47:14.298 --> 47:17.062
- we'll go and find this Hawksin hotel.
- Careful, careful.

47:19.102 --> 47:22.162
- Rajiv Uncle!
- Who's this man talking to me like this?

47:22.339 --> 47:25.172
- I'm Sajarit from Punjab.
- Okay, how...

47:25.242 --> 47:28.109
I know it has been a little while
since Navinda's wedding, but...

47:28.178 --> 47:30.806
Your family owns that store in Hoboken.

47:30.881 --> 47:32.041
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

47:32.115 --> 47:34.447
- And she's my wife, Neha.
- Hello, <i>namaste.</i>

47:34.518 --> 47:36.679
And you are here
for Rani Auntie's birthday.

47:36.753 --> 47:38.778
Of course, of course,
and we are getting late

47:38.856 --> 47:40.847
and we have to find a cab
and get our luggage first.

47:40.924 --> 47:42.448
Come, come, come.
I'll give you a ride in my car.

47:42.526 --> 47:44.426
No, no, no! We don't want a ride!

47:44.494 --> 47:46.485
My parents will be furious
if I did not give a ride.

47:46.563 --> 47:49.430
- Please, come with me. My car is quite big.
- No, no, no... It's fine, thank you.

47:49.499 --> 47:50.989
My car is fast. Neha, please hold this.

47:51.068 --> 47:52.365
- Okay.
- Come, come. Come, come, come.

47:52.436 --> 47:54.529
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. Okay, I'll help you.
- It's fine! It's fine...

47:54.605 --> 47:57.267
It's so good to see you.
Come, please, excuse me.

47:57.341 --> 48:01.038
And this is a most pleasant
surprise for us. Please accept tea.

48:01.111 --> 48:03.409
We thought, since you were coming
all the way from here

48:03.480 --> 48:06.574
to Mumbai for Priya's wedding,

48:06.650 --> 48:11.246
we thought it was important that we also
show our respects, by coming to...

48:11.321 --> 48:15.849
<i>Han ji.</i> You know, but we are only sorry
that Priya and Govinda couldn't come.

48:15.959 --> 48:19.656
- Priya is visiting friends.
- Friends.

48:20.631 --> 48:24.931
And Govinda, you know, so
busy with exams and cricket and all that.

48:25.002 --> 48:26.970
- His final exam's going on.
<i>- Han ji. Han ji.</i>

48:46.990 --> 48:50.426
Hi, sorry to disturb you.
Delivery for Priya Sethi.

48:50.494 --> 48:53.486
- Really? Thank you.
- Here you go.

49:06.276 --> 49:08.642
Anji, where is your boom box?

49:09.713 --> 49:11.681
- She's asleep.
- Okay.

49:13.216 --> 49:18.313
All right, we will find this Hotel Hawkskin
as quickly as possible.

49:18.388 --> 49:21.186
- Yeah.
- There, we will divide,

49:21.591 --> 49:23.684
locate Priya and take her home.

49:24.227 --> 49:27.094
Pimmi, you will stay here.
If there's a problem, we'll call you.

49:27.164 --> 49:29.860
- No, no, no, no. I'm coming with you.
- Let her come, <i>ji.</i>

49:29.933 --> 49:31.798
- Okay. Huh?
- Rajiv? Where is he?

49:31.868 --> 49:33.768
- Hello.
- Hello.

49:33.837 --> 49:36.670
Oh, there you are.
Rajiv, please come down.

49:36.773 --> 49:40.800
Anji wants to show her dance. She's been
practicing specially for Rani Auntie.

49:40.877 --> 49:44.643
But, <i>Auntie ji's</i> sleeping.
I don't think it's nice to disturb her.

49:44.715 --> 49:48.583
Let her sleep. She sleeps through
everything. You, come down. Come.

49:48.652 --> 49:50.950
- Now?
- Oh, yeah. Why not?

49:51.621 --> 49:53.384
- Right now?
- Oh, yeah. Right now.

49:53.457 --> 49:57.052
Come on, she's all set with her music
in her hand. Please, Rajiv.

49:58.695 --> 50:00.595
Come on, Anji. Play some music. Come on.

50:03.066 --> 50:04.727
Shake it, Anji!

50:06.136 --> 50:08.434
Isn't she wonderful, Rajiv?

50:11.208 --> 50:12.800
Come on, do it!

50:14.811 --> 50:18.372
Oh, I forgot. The Sawants are coming over
for dinner tonight.

50:38.602 --> 50:42.197
<i>Some day</i>

50:42.873 --> 50:46.536
<i>When I'm awfully low</i>

50:47.344 --> 50:51.280
<i>When the world is cold</i>

50:51.948 --> 50:54.610
<i>I will feel a glow</i>

50:54.684 --> 50:59.951
<i>Just thinking of you</i>

51:00.824 --> 51:07.423
<i>And the way you look tonight</i>

51:15.806 --> 51:17.239
<i>Lovely</i>

51:17.340 --> 51:18.739
Who's that?

51:20.343 --> 51:21.867
Just a friend.

51:22.579 --> 51:24.740
First impressions can be deceiving.

51:24.815 --> 51:27.113
- The thing about this guy...
- Here we go.

51:27.184 --> 51:30.551
...he's all casual charm
like nothing gets to him,

51:30.620 --> 51:32.986
but really, complete softie.

51:33.056 --> 51:34.614
- Yeah?
- In college,

51:34.691 --> 51:38.889
he couldn't eat or sleep until this
girl he liked finally talked to him.

51:38.962 --> 51:41.522
- I think he actually threw up afterwards.
- What?

51:41.598 --> 51:43.395
The man knows
how to make an impression.

51:43.467 --> 51:45.435
Wait, let me give you a little advice.

51:45.502 --> 51:47.094
Don't listen to drunk Americans.

51:47.170 --> 51:49.138
No, but I do agree with Charlie.

51:49.206 --> 51:52.198
You know, there's something more
than what you really show.

51:52.275 --> 51:54.436
What about you? Any secrets?

51:54.511 --> 51:58.345
Are you an Indian movie star
hiding in America as a tourist?

51:59.249 --> 52:01.774
Well, glad you could make it.
Enjoying yourselves, I hope?

52:01.852 --> 52:03.683
- Definitely. Thank you, sir.
- Thank you.

52:04.554 --> 52:06.044
It's a wonderful party.

52:06.123 --> 52:08.489
Same feeling as the rest of your hotels,

52:08.558 --> 52:11.425
a magical oasis
that springs from nowhere.

52:11.495 --> 52:13.588
It's so familiar.

52:13.663 --> 52:15.062
We need you now.

52:15.132 --> 52:16.724
Maybe I should hire her
for my ad campaign.

52:18.168 --> 52:19.635
She's a smart girl.

52:21.171 --> 52:23.366
- He's kidding, right?
- Yeah, he's kidding.

52:24.975 --> 52:26.602
Have fun, buddy.

52:27.777 --> 52:28.766
It's okay.

52:30.647 --> 52:33.616
Look, but don't touch.
Look, but don't touch.

52:34.017 --> 52:35.985
Do you know, when I was little,

52:36.052 --> 52:39.852
I always wanted to find the golden ticket
in that chocolate,

52:39.923 --> 52:42.187
like Willy Wonka,

52:43.793 --> 52:46.421
so that I could go somewhere new.

52:47.631 --> 52:49.758
I always wanted to know
who was gonna drink that chocolate

52:49.833 --> 52:52.393
- after the fat kid fell in it.
- Yeah.

52:54.204 --> 52:56.695
Did you just try to push me in?

52:56.773 --> 52:58.866
That was a tap and you're too heavy.

52:58.942 --> 53:01.172
You see,
I knew there was another side to you.

53:01.244 --> 53:05.112
On the outside, you're the psychic,
sweet nurse from India,

53:06.283 --> 53:08.080
but you've got a streak.

53:11.555 --> 53:14.820
You're right.
There are things you should know.

53:19.462 --> 53:21.327
- Talk. Talk.
- Are you mad?

53:21.398 --> 53:23.229
- No.
- Talk.

53:23.300 --> 53:24.961
I'll throw you in.

53:26.803 --> 53:29.101
I forgot to watch out
for drunk Americans.

53:31.341 --> 53:32.433
Oh, there you are.

53:32.509 --> 53:34.340
Listen, I know, I know,
I'm sorry to interrupt.

53:34.411 --> 53:36.208
Business first, I need you for a second.

53:36.279 --> 53:38.008
One of us will be right back.

53:46.022 --> 53:48.047
- Gee.
- What's up, buddy?

53:48.959 --> 53:52.451
- I just put something together.
- Oh, yeah? What's that?

53:53.230 --> 53:55.289
Well, call me cynical,

53:56.099 --> 53:58.863
but did you bring your Indian friend
Prius here...

53:58.935 --> 54:00.800
- Priya.
- Whatever.

54:00.870 --> 54:04.772
To show Hawksin you're some
free-thinking, international guy?

54:04.841 --> 54:07.332
"Look at me, I'm dating an Indian girl."

54:07.410 --> 54:10.004
Yeah, you...
You figured me out, Chuck.

54:10.080 --> 54:11.980
Oh, yeah.

54:14.484 --> 54:16.076
All right, all right.

54:21.291 --> 54:23.384
Priya! Priya, wait!

54:27.264 --> 54:29.562
- Where are you going?
- I'm going back.

54:30.834 --> 54:32.495
